text: @realmoney Moved Back to Market Neutral * Just a little fine tuning * I will sleep well tonite Given my Bearish predilections I feel uncomfortable being even small net long so I just made a minor portfolio adjustment. To accomplish this, (with $SPY at $297.75 and $QQQ at $190.30)

I have purchased some (defined risk) and slightly out of the money SPY and QQQ puts (with 1-2 month expirations). The delta-adjusted impact is to move me back to market neutral. @tomkeene @jimcramer @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney

@realmoney The Look of a Contrarian and Not a Cassandra * Mr. Market is a dynamic and complex mosaic - providing opportunities on both the long and short side For those that think me dogmatically bearish, a Cassandra (if you will) - consider my moves today.

Besides my short covers ($SPY and $QQQ) and put sales I have picked up the following long add-ons (at very good prices) in the early market dip - $TWTR, $FB, $AMZN and $GOOGL. As of now I am slightly net long in exposure (!) - but I don't expect this to be a permanent

condition by any stretch of the imagination, as I will be shorting strength! The market is a dynamic and complex mosaic - providing opportunities both side of the pew. Always. And especially for the opportunistic trader and investor @tomkeene @jimcramer @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney

@realmoney Calling an Audible * I covered all my Index shorts * Moved back to market neutral I am taking off all of my remaining Index shorts for a substantial gain. This is, in large measure, a gut and instinctive call - something I don't do often.

However, my hunch is that I will have an opportunity to reshort the Indices on strength. Moreover, in such a "newsy" backdrop (re the impeachment inquiry) I would prefer to have much smaller exposure - I want to reduce my portfolio's VAR (value at risk).
This dramatic moves takes me back to Market Neutral in exposure. I still remain negative over the balance of the year. $SPY $QQQ @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney

@realmoney With SPYDERs trading at about $294.60 I am covering half of my $SPY and $QQQ shorts (taking them from large to medium) and taking in my put SPY and QQQ options - all for a nice profit. I suspect I could have an opportunity to reshort the Indices at somewhat higher

levels. This is part of my continued process of trading around Index shorts. I am now back down to medium sized in my net short exposure - from very large. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney
